 First of all, the falling liquidus lines are examples of 
\begin_inset Quotes eld
\end_inset

freezing point lowering.
\begin_inset Quotes erd
\end_inset

 This important phenomenon is used to advantage on icy streets by applying
 salt, which lowers the freezing point of ice.
 Of course, this requires that the ice melt and the liquid dissolve some
 salt as component 
\begin_inset Quotes eld
\end_inset

B
\begin_inset Quotes erd
\end_inset

 in Figure 
