\begin_inset Quotes eld
\end_inset

dry,
\begin_inset Quotes erd
\end_inset

 which is a common (and disastrous!) misconception.
 Cement 
\begin_inset Quotes eld
\end_inset

hydration
\begin_inset Quotes erd
\end_inset

/hardening actually consumes water, so once initial 
\begin_inset Quotes eld
\end_inset

set
\begin_inset Quotes erd
\end_inset

 has taken place, gently hose is down (or cover it with plastic) to keep
