\begin_layout Standard
The point here is that 
\begin_inset Formula $C_{2}S$
\end_inset

 and 
\begin_inset Formula $C_{3}S$
\end_inset

 are man-made compounds, and their manufacture depends upon 
\begin_inset Quotes eld
\end_inset

freezing point lowering.
\begin_inset Quotes erd
\end_inset

 Both compounds have melting points in excess of 
\begin_inset Formula $2000^{o}C$
\end_inset

, higher than just about any low-cost 
