\begin_layout Standard
In order to compare the free energies of two or more phases in Type II phase
 diagrams, we need to plot absolute free energies rather than the free energy
 change upon mixing (
\begin_inset Formula $\Delta G^{M}$
\end_inset

) as in Figure 
\begin_inset CommandInset ref
LatexCommand ref
reference "fig:SolvusPlot"

\end_inset

.
 Before working with such diagrams, however, we need to have two more thermodyna
mic 
\begin_inset Quotes eld
\end_inset

tools
\begin_inset Quotes erd
\end_inset

 in our toolbox.
