\begin_layout Standard
On the other hand, the temperature 
\begin_inset Formula $T_{2}$
\end_inset

 is below the eutectic temperature.
 The free energy vs.
 compostion curve for the liquid solution lies everywhere above those of
 the two solid solutions.
 The lowest free energy situation is either a single solid solution by itself,
 namely 
\begin_inset Formula $\alpha$
\end_inset

 solid solution or 
\begin_inset Formula $\beta$
\end_inset

 solid solution on the left and right ends of the phase diagram, respectively,
 or a microstructure incorporating both 
\begin_inset Formula $\alpha$
\end_inset

 and 
\begin_inset Formula $\beta$
\end_inset

 solid solutions in the middle of the phase diagram.
 Their equilibrium is reflected in the common tangent line between their
