) is on the order of 
\begin_inset Formula $10^{13}/s$
\end_inset

.
 We can look at this frequency as the 
\begin_inset Quotes eld
\end_inset

attempt
\begin_inset Quotes erd
\end_inset

 frequency, or how many times per second the interstitial is attempting
 to jump from the original position to the new one.
 So only approximately 2 out of 10,000 attempts is successful at this temperatur
e.
