\begin_layout Subsection
Semi-Infinite Systems
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
By 
\begin_inset Quotes eld
\end_inset

semi-infinite
\begin_inset Quotes erd
\end_inset

 systems we are referring to situations where the specimen can be treated
 as essentially 
\begin_inset Quotes eld
\end_inset

infinite
\begin_inset Quotes erd
\end_inset

 in size compared to the extent of the impurity concentration profile at
 the surface.
 Another way of describing this is that the concentration profile resulting
 from diffusion never reaches the other end of the specimen.
 The specimen, although not infinite in extent, is effectively 
\begin_inset Quotes eld
\end_inset

infinite
\begin_inset Quotes erd
\end_inset

 insofar as diffusion is concerned.
 In terms of diffusion it is 
\begin_inset Quotes eld
\end_inset

semi-infinite.
\begin_inset Quotes erd
\end_inset


