\begin_layout Subsubsection
Thin Film Tracer Diffusion
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
Thin film 
\begin_inset Quotes eld
\end_inset

tracer
\begin_inset Quotes erd
\end_inset

 diffusion is of special importance to materials science and engineering.
 It is how diffusion coefficients are often measured.
 Imagine a thin film containing an area concentration (
\begin_inset Formula $\#/cm^{2}$
\end_inset

) of a 
\begin_inset Quotes eld
\end_inset

tracer
\begin_inset Quotes erd
\end_inset

 that is deposited on a highly polished, flat surface of a single crystal
 (crystal #1 in Figure 
\begin_inset CommandInset ref
LatexCommand ref
reference "fig:TracerDiff"

\end_inset

).
 To prevent any loss of 
\begin_inset Quotes eld
\end_inset

tracer
\begin_inset Quotes erd
\end_inset

 (for example by evaporation) and also to provide a second crystal in which
 to study diffusion, the highly polished, flat surface of crystal #2 in
 Figure 
\begin_inset CommandInset ref
LatexCommand ref
reference "fig:TracerDiff"

\end_inset

 is butted up against crystal #1, sandwiching the tracer thin film between
 them.
 For self-diffusion studies, the tracer is the same chemical species as
 constitutes both crystals, however with a different atomic mass (namely,
 another isotope than that of the host atoms making up the two crystals).
 In many instances, a radioactive tracer is employed at low concentrations
 (and low radioactive emission levels to protect lab workers).
 In this case, the relative concentration of tracer at a specific diffusion
 depth is determined by the number of radioactive 
\begin_inset Quotes eld
\end_inset

counts
\begin_inset Quotes erd
\end_inset

 registered at that depth, usually by 
\begin_inset Quotes eld
\end_inset

serial sectioning
\begin_inset Quotes erd
\end_inset

 (see below).
 In other cases, the amount of a non-radioactive tracer diffused to a given
 depth can be established by the use of a mass spectrometer that can differentia
te and quantify the relative amounts of tracer species vs.
 naturally occurring (host crystal) species.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
\begin_inset Float figure
placement h
wide false
sideways false
status open

\begin_layout Plain Layout
\noindent
\align center
\begin_inset Graphics
	filename figures/TracerDiff.svg
	lyxscale 40
	scale 80

\end_inset


\end_layout

