\begin_layout Standard
You will see one special composition highlighted, labeled 
\begin_inset Formula $c_{0.5}$
\end_inset

.
 This corresponds to the point where the composition is half way between
 the surface composition (
\begin_inset Formula $c_{s}$
\end_inset

) and the original sample composition (
\begin_inset Formula $c_{o}$
\end_inset

), which modifies equation 
\begin_inset CommandInset ref
LatexCommand ref
reference "eq:erfCarb2level2"

\end_inset

 to equation 
\begin_inset CommandInset ref
LatexCommand ref
reference "eq:C0.5"

\end_inset

:
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
\begin_inset Formula 
\begin{equation}
