 Hence, automotive oxygen sensors are typically referred to as lambda-sensors.
 It should be noted that given the different cation valence (4+ in 
\begin_inset Formula $TiO_{2}$
\end_inset

 vs.
 2+ for MO), and therefore the different charge on an interstitial cation,
 the slope on a log-log plot of G vs.
 
\begin_inset Formula $p_{O_{2}}$
\end_inset

 was not the -1/6 for titania.
 Nevertheless, the invention of a resistance-based oxygen sensor was an
 important development.
